						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine, Kṛipāpurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10: 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Worn out and built in. It registers a sale of <hi rend="italic">kollai</hi> (kitchen-garden) land made tax-free by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tiruveṇṇainallūr on receiving the price and the capital against taxes, to one Aparājitaṉ-Uttamaśōḻa Mārāyaṉ of Perumūr for being endowed by him to the temple as <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna.</hi></p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 265.</p>						

						</summary>
